<subSubSection lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,1863,2010]" lastBlockId="51.[151,1436,152,338]" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,326,1863,1889]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Observations:</emphasis>
The taxonomic status of this species should be reevaluated on the basis of comparative evidence between its 
<typeStatus box="[377,427,1904,1930]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
series and specimens of the Patagonian species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" authorityYear="1938" box="[1021,1252,1904,1929]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetschi">
<emphasis box="[1021,1252,1904,1929]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Liolaemus goetschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. When 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala, C. S." pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="3 - 32" refId="ref50071" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2003) Cuatro nuevas especies del genero Liolaemus (Iguania: Liolaemidae), pertenecientes al grupo boulengeri, de la Patagonia, Argentina. Cuadernos de Herpetologia, 17, 3 - 32." type="journal article" year="2003">Abdala (2003)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdala" authorityYear="2003" box="[351,480,1944,1969]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="martorii">
<emphasis box="[351,480,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">L. martorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species, the taxon 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" authorityYear="1938" box="[811,940,1944,1969]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetschi">
<emphasis box="[811,940,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">L. goetschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was still considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Etheridge" authorityYear="1993" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanops">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">L. melanops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[238,280,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">e.g.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cei, J. M." box="[289,400,1984,2010]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref54786" refString="Cei, J. M. (1986) Reptiles del centro, centro-oeste y sur de la Argentina. Herpetofauna de las zonas aridas y semiaridas. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, Monografie 4, 528 pp." type="book" year="1986">Cei 1986</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, 
<bibRefCitation author="Scolaro, J. A. &amp; Cei, J. M." box="[588,842,1984,2010]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="107 - 112" refId="ref72364" refString="Scolaro, J. A. &amp; Cei, J. M. (2003) Una excepcional nueva especie de Phymaturus de la precordillera de Chubut, Argentina (Liolaemidae, Iguania, Lacertilia, Reptilia). Facena, 19, 107 - 112." type="journal article" year="2003">Cei &amp; Scolaro (2003)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" authorityYear="1938" box="[1027,1156,1984,2009]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetschi">
<emphasis box="[1027,1156,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">L. goetschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Etheridge" authorityYear="1993" box="[1214,1358,1984,2009]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanops">
<emphasis box="[1214,1358,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">L. melanops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
repre- sent two different species. This might explain why 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala, C. S." box="[764,935,152,178]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="3 - 32" refId="ref50071" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2003) Cuatro nuevas especies del genero Liolaemus (Iguania: Liolaemidae), pertenecientes al grupo boulengeri, de la Patagonia, Argentina. Cuadernos de Herpetologia, 17, 3 - 32." type="journal article" year="2003">Abdala (2003)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide comparisons between the populations identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" authorityYear="1938" box="[445,574,192,217]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetschi">
<emphasis box="[445,574,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">L. goetschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdala" authorityYear="2003" box="[630,758,192,217]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="martorii">
<emphasis box="[630,758,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">L. martorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Morphological and field observations between these two taxa carried out by one of us (JAS) suggest that they may be conspecific. Distribution, morphology and coloration exhibit strong overlap between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" authorityYear="1938" box="[603,734,272,297]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetschi">
<emphasis box="[603,734,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">L. goetschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdala" authorityYear="2003" box="[798,930,272,297]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="martorii">
<emphasis box="[798,930,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">L. martorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The problem should be reassessed using appropriate statistical analyses.
</paragraph>
